This paper deals with combinatorial and graph-theoretic aspects of phylogenetic trees, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of flag algebras also suggests a connection to cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The study of phylogenetic trees is also relevant to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
